Description: # in-container [![PyPI version](https://badge.fury.io/py/in-container.svg)](https://badge.fury.io/py/in-container)[![Build Status](https://travis-ci.com/ZiggerZZ/in_container.svg?branch=master)](https://travis-ci.com/ZiggerZZ/in_container)[![codecov](https://codecov.io/gh/ZiggerZZ/in_container/branch/master/graph/badge.svg)](https://codecov.io/gh/ZiggerZZ/in_container)
        
        > Allows you to check if your program is running inside a Docker container
        
        ## Install
        
        ```
        $ pip install in-container
        ```
        
        ## Usage
        
        ```python
        from in_container import in_container
        print(in_container()) # True or False
        ```
        
